Agent Instructions for SkemaBase

This file contains guidance for the agent when working on the SkemaBase codebase.
End-user documentation (syntax, grammar, usage examples) resides in README.md and docs/CLI.md.

Key locations:
- skemabase-js/src: source modules (tokenizer, parser, astToIR, sql, index)
- skemabase-js/tests: Jest unit tests
- bin/cli.js: command-line integration

Developer workflow:
- Create a new branch per feature or phase
- Use `apply_patch` to modify files; keep changes minimal and focused
- Write red–green tests (Jest) before implementation; aim for high coverage
- Add JSDoc comments for any new public API
- Update README.md and docs/ with user-facing changes (CLI flags, examples)
- Run `cd skemabase-js && npm install && npm test && npm run lint` to validate
- After implementation:
  • Remove debug code and inline comments
  • Ensure pre-commit checks pass
  • Commit with clear message, push branch, and open a PR (`gh pr create`)

Coding guidelines:
- Fix root causes, avoid quick hacks
- Keep code style consistent with the existing codebase
- Document any new behavior or flags
- Add tests for edge cases and error handling

Use this file as the agent’s cheat sheet; defer all user-facing details to the official docs.
